# SOHO Network Configuration

This repository contains a complete small office / home office (SOHO) network setup.

## Features
- Router configuration (OpenWRT style)
- VLAN segmentation
- DHCP & DNS setup
- Firewall rules
- Secure WiFi configuration
- Basic monitoring setup

## Network Segments
- LAN: 192.168.1.0/24
- Guest: 192.168.10.0/24
- IoT: 192.168.20.0/24

## Hardware Assumptions
- Router: OpenWRT-compatible device
- Switch: Managed (VLAN capable)
- Access Point: Supports multiple SSIDs

## Goals
- Security
- Segmentation
- Simplicity


1. Rouer Config

config interface 'lan'
    option proto 'static'
    option ipaddr '192.168.1.1'
    option netmask '255.255.255.0'

config interface 'guest'
    option proto 'static'
    option ipaddr '192.168.10.1'
    option netmask '255.255.255.0'

config interface 'iot'
    option proto 'static'
    option ipaddr '192.168.20.1'
    option netmask '255.255.255.0'

2. Firewall Rules 
#!/bin/sh

# Default policies
iptables -P INPUT DROP
iptables -P FORWARD DROP
iptables -P OUTPUT ACCEPT

# Allow LAN full access
iptables -A FORWARD -s 192.168.1.0/24 -j ACCEPT

# Allow Guest → Internet only
iptables -A FORWARD -s 192.168.10.0/24 -d 192.168.1.0/24 -j DROP
iptables -A FORWARD -s 192.168.10.0/24 -j ACCEPT

# IoT isolation
iptables -A FORWARD -s 192.168.20.0/24 -d 192.168.1.0/24 -j DROP
iptables -A FORWARD -s 192.168.20.0/24 -j ACCEPT

# Allow established connections
iptables -A FORWARD -m state --state ESTABLISHED,RELATED -j ACCEPT

3. DHCP Config

subnet 192.168.1.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {
    range 192.168.1.100 192.168.1.200;
    option routers 192.168.1.1;
}

subnet 192.168.10.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {
    range 192.168.10.100 192.168.10.200;
    option routers 192.168.10.1;
}

subnet 192.168.20.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {
    range 192.168.20.100 192.168.20.200;
    option routers 192.168.20.1;
}

4. DNS Config
domain-needed
bogus-priv
no-resolv
server=8.8.8.8
server=1.1.1.1

local=/home.lan/
expand-hosts

5. VLAN Setup
VLAN 1: LAN
VLAN 10: Guest
VLAN 20: IoT

Switch Port Config:
Port 1: Trunk (Router)
Port 2-3: LAN
Port 4: Guest AP
Port 5: IoT Devices

